## PART 2 — MONOREPO ROOT STRUCTURE

```
/
├── cmd/                        # Executable entrypoints — one dir per binary
│   ├── taskapi/
│   │   └── main.go             # Wire deps, call run(). Max 80 lines.
│   └── worker/
│       └── main.go
│
├── internal/                   # Private application packages (non-importable externally)
│   ├── taskapi/                # HTTP server assembly for taskapi binary
│   ├── tasktestdb/             # Test DB helpers (SQLite)
│   ├── envload/                # .env loading and resolution
│   ├── httpsecurity/           # Security header middleware and tests
│   └── handlertest/            # Shared HTTP test helpers
│
├── pkgs/                       # Domain packages — importable by multiple binaries
│   ├── tasks/                  # Core task domain (see Part 3)
│   ├── agents/                 # Agent orchestration domain
│   └── repo/                   # Workspace/repo abstraction
│
├── web/                        # React/TypeScript frontend (see Part 4)
│
├── docs/                       # Architecture decision records and contracts
│   ├── API-HTTP.md             # REST contract (authoritative)
│   ├── API-SSE.md              # SSE contract (authoritative)
│   ├── DESIGN.md               # Hub document — links all others
│   ├── PERSISTENCE.md
│   ├── RUNTIME-ENV.md
│   ├── OBSERVABILITY.md
│   └── adr/                    # Architecture Decision Records (ADR-NNNN.md)
│
├── scripts/                    # Build, check, and dev scripts
│   ├── check.sh
│   └── check.ps1
│
├── .agent/                     # Autonomous agent logs and snapshots (gitignored)
├── .cursor/                    # Cursor IDE rules
├── go.mod
├── go.sum
└── README.md
```

### Root-Level Rules

- `cmd/` contains only entrypoints. If you find business logic in `cmd/`, move it before adding more.
- `internal/` is for packages used by exactly one binary or for cross-cutting concerns that must not be externally imported.
- `pkgs/` is for domain packages potentially used by multiple binaries. Do not put HTTP-specific code in `pkgs/`.
- Every top-level directory must have a one-line description in `DESIGN.md`.
- Add a new top-level directory only when it represents a distinct deployable or importable boundary, and you have written the `docs/` entry first.

