## PART 3 — GO PACKAGE STRUCTURE (PER DOMAIN)

Each domain package in `pkgs/` follows this canonical layout:

```
pkgs/tasks/
├── domain/
│   ├── task.go                 # Task type, status/priority enums, validation
│   ├── cycle.go                # Cycle and phase types
│   ├── errors.go               # ErrNotFound, ErrInvalidInput, etc.
│   └── transitions.go          # State machine validation functions
│
├── store/
│   ├── store.go                # Store struct, constructor, interface compliance check
│   ├── store_tasks.go          # Task CRUD
│   ├── store_cycles.go         # Cycle CRUD + dual-write
│   ├── store_cycle_phases.go   # Phase CRUD + dual-write
│   └── store_events.go         # task_events append
│
├── handler/
│   ├── handler.go              # Handler struct, constructor, route registration
│   ├── handler_tasks.go        # /tasks routes
│   ├── handler_cycles.go       # /cycles routes
│   ├── handler_sse.go          # /events SSE endpoint
│   ├── handler_health.go       # /health endpoints
│   ├── handler_tasks_json.go   # Request/response types for tasks
│   ├── handler_cycles_json.go  # Request/response types for cycles
│   ├── hub.go                  # SSE subscriber hub
│   └── middleware.go           # Handler-local middleware
│
├── middleware/
│   ├── stack.go                # Stack() — ordered middleware assembly
│   ├── middleware_recovery.go
│   ├── middleware_logger.go
│   ├── middleware_metrics.go
│   └── middleware_requestid.go
│
├── service/                    # Orchestration layer (when needed)
│   └── task_service.go
│
├── postgres/
│   └── migrate.go
│
└── README.md                   # Maps files to routes/responsibilities
```

### Go File-Size Limits

| Zone | Green | Yellow (justify or split) | Red (must split) |
|------|-------|---------------------------|------------------|
| `cmd/*/main.go` | ≤ 80 lines | 81–120 | > 120 |
| Domain types (`domain/*.go`) | ≤ 200 lines | 201–350 | > 350 |
| Store files (`store_*.go`) | ≤ 300 lines | 301–500 | > 500 |
| Handler files (`handler_*.go`) | ≤ 300 lines | 301–500 | > 500 |
| JSON/DTO files (`*_json.go`) | ≤ 200 lines | 201–350 | > 350 |
| Middleware files | ≤ 150 lines | 151–250 | > 250 |
| Service files | ≤ 300 lines | 301–450 | > 450 |
| Test files (`*_test.go`) | ≤ 400 lines | 401–600 | > 600 |
| General application code | ≤ 400 lines | 401–700 | > 800 |

Generated code (`// Code generated … DO NOT EDIT`, sqlc, protobuf, stringer) is exempt from all limits. Add a file-level comment so reviewers do not flag it.

### Go Package Rules

- A package name must describe what it provides, never what it is (`store` not `datastorepackage`).
- A `store_*.go` file maps 1:1 to a database entity. If one entity's store methods exceed Red, split by operation: `store_tasks_read.go` / `store_tasks_write.go`.
- A `handler_*.go` file maps 1:1 to a resource group. Never mix `/tasks` and `/cycles` handlers in one file.
- Create `*_json.go` files immediately when a handler file has more than 3 inline request/response types.
- Never put SQL in handler files. Never put HTTP logic in store files. This is an enforced boundary.
- When a domain grows beyond one team's working context, split it into its own `pkgs/` entry with its own full subtree.

