### Feature Module Structure

Each feature is a vertical slice. It owns its components, hooks, and local types. It may import from `src/components/`, `src/api/`, `src/types/`, and `src/hooks/` — never from another feature module.

```
features/tasks/
├── index.ts                    # Public barrel export — the only import surface
├── TasksPage.tsx               # Route-level container. Max 80 lines.
├── TasksPage.test.tsx
│
├── components/
│   ├── TaskList.tsx
│   ├── TaskList.test.tsx
│   ├── TaskCard.tsx
│   ├── TaskCard.test.tsx
│   ├── TaskDetail.tsx
│   └── TaskForm.tsx
│
├── hooks/
│   ├── useTask.ts
│   ├── useTasks.ts
│   ├── useCreateTask.ts
│   ├── useUpdateTask.ts
│   └── useDeleteTask.ts
│
├── stores/
│   └── useTaskUIStore.ts       # Selection state, filter state
│
└── types/
    └── taskFilters.ts          # Types NOT shared outside this feature
```

### TypeScript/React File-Size Limits

| Zone | Green | Yellow (justify or split) | Red (must split) |
|------|-------|---------------------------|------------------|
| Route-level page (`*Page.tsx`) | ≤ 80 lines | 81–150 | > 150 |
| Container components | ≤ 120 lines | 121–200 | > 200 |
| Presentational components | ≤ 150 lines | 151–250 | > 250 |
| Custom hooks (`use*.ts`) | ≤ 80 lines | 81–150 | > 150 |
| API client files (`api/*.ts`) | ≤ 200 lines | 201–350 | > 350 |
| Utility files (`utils/*.ts`) | ≤ 150 lines | 151–250 | > 250 |
| Type definition files | ≤ 200 lines | 201–400 | > 400 |
| Test files (`*.test.tsx`) | ≤ 300 lines | 301–500 | > 500 |
| CSS files (per component) | ≤ 200 lines | 201–350 | > 350 |
| `tokens.css` / global CSS | ≤ 500 lines | — | > 700 (split by category) |

### TypeScript Module Boundary Rules

- **Feature modules are closed.** `features/tasks/` may not import from `features/cycles/`. Shared concepts belong in `src/types/` or `src/api/`.
- **Barrel exports are the public API.** Each feature's `index.ts` is the only allowed import surface. Deep imports into another feature (`features/tasks/hooks/useTask`) are a boundary violation.
- **`src/api/` is the only place that calls `fetch`.** All server responses are `unknown` until parsed through the response parser in that file.
- **`src/components/` is domain-agnostic.** If a component in `src/components/` imports from `src/types/task.ts`, it has leaked into the feature domain — move it to `features/tasks/components/`.
- **`src/hooks/` contains only hooks with no feature dependency.** A hook that imports from `src/api/tasks.ts` belongs in `features/tasks/hooks/`.

