## PART 7 — NAMING CONVENTIONS AT SCALE

### Go Naming

| Entity | Convention | Example |
|--------|------------|---------|
| Package | Lowercase single word | `store`, `domain`, `handler` |
| File | Snake_case | `store_tasks.go`, `handler_cycles_json.go` |
| Type | PascalCase noun | `Task`, `CyclePhase`, `PostgresTaskStore` |
| Interface | PascalCase behavior noun | `TaskStore`, `Notifier`, `Clock` |
| Constructor | `New` or `New<Type>` | `NewHandler(deps)` |
| Error variable | `Err` prefix | `ErrNotFound`, `ErrInvalidInput` |
| Test function | `Test<Type>_<method>_<scenario>` | `TestStore_GetByID_returns_not_found` |
| Test helper | lowercase descriptive | `newTestServer(t)`, `seedTask(t, db)` |

### TypeScript/React Naming

| Entity | Convention | Example |
|--------|------------|---------|
| Feature directory | Lowercase plural noun | `tasks/`, `cycles/` |
| Component file | PascalCase `.tsx` | `TaskCard.tsx` |
| Hook file | camelCase `use` prefix `.ts` | `useTask.ts` |
| API file | camelCase resource noun | `tasks.ts` |
| Type file | camelCase concept noun | `task.ts`, `apiContracts.ts` |
| Utility file | camelCase noun | `formatters.ts`, `validators.ts` |
| Test file | Same name + `.test` | `TaskCard.test.tsx` |
| MSW handler | Resource noun | `test/handlers/tasks.ts` |
| Factory file | Resource noun | `test/factories/task.ts` |

### Universal Naming Rules

- A file name must describe its primary export or responsibility. If you cannot name it without using "and" or "or", the file is doing too much.
- Test files live next to their source file. Never in a separated top-level `__tests__/` folder.
- Never use `utils.ts`, `helpers.go`, `common.ts`, or `shared.go` as dumping grounds.
- Avoid abbreviations except universally understood ones (`id`, `url`, `http`, `ctx`, `cfg`).

