## PART 8 — DEPENDENCY DIRECTION ENFORCEMENT

### Go Dependency Graph

```
cmd/*
  └── imports → internal/*
                  └── imports → pkgs/*/handler
                                  └── imports → pkgs/*/store
                                                  └── imports → pkgs/*/domain
                                                                  └── (stdlib only)
```

- `domain` imports: stdlib only. No DB drivers. No HTTP packages.
- `store` imports: `domain` + DB driver + stdlib. No HTTP packages.
- `handler` imports: `domain` + `store` interfaces + HTTP stdlib. No DB drivers.
- `internal` imports: any `pkgs/*` package. Wires them together.
- `cmd` imports: `internal/*` only. Max 80 lines.

### TypeScript Dependency Graph

```
app/ (routing, providers)
  └── imports → features/*/index.ts
                  └── imports → src/api/, src/types/, src/components/, src/hooks/
                                  └── imports → src/utils/, src/styles/
                                                  └── (no src/ imports)
```

- `src/utils/` imports: nothing from `src/`. Pure TypeScript.
- `src/types/` imports: nothing from `src/`. Type-only.
- `src/api/` imports: `src/types/` only. No component imports.
- `src/components/` imports: `src/types/`, `src/utils/`, `src/hooks/`. Never `src/api/`. Never `features/`.
- `features/*/` imports: `src/api/`, `src/types/`, `src/components/`, `src/hooks/`. Never another feature.
- `app/` imports: `features/*/index.ts` public surface only.

### CI Violation Checks

Add these to your CI pipeline:

```bash
# Go: detect handler importing db driver directly
grep -rn "database/sql\|lib/pq\|jackc/pgx" pkgs/tasks/handler/ --include="*.go"

# Go: detect domain importing http or db
grep -rn "net/http\|database/sql\|gorm" pkgs/tasks/domain/ --include="*.go"

# TypeScript: detect feature importing another feature
grep -rn "from '.*features/" web/src/features/ --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx" \
  | grep -v "from '\.\." | grep -v "from '\./\|from '\.\./\."

# TypeScript: detect fetch outside api/
grep -rn "fetch(" web/src/ --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx" \
  | grep -v "web/src/api/" | grep -v "test/"
```

