## PART 10 — FILE MIGRATION CHECKLIST

When a file hits Red during review, complete this before splitting:

- [ ] Write the primary responsibility of the file in one sentence.
- [ ] List every function/type and label it with the responsibility it serves.
- [ ] Group by responsibility. Any group with a clear name is a split candidate.
- [ ] Verify the proposed split does not create a circular import.
- [ ] Verify each resulting file would be > 30 lines.
- [ ] Name the split files before creating them. If you cannot name one, reconsider.
- [ ] Create the split files in the same package unless dependency direction requires otherwise.
- [ ] Move functions without rewriting them — rewrites are a separate commit.
- [ ] Update all imports.
- [ ] Run `go test ./...` or `npm test -- --run`. Must pass before committing.
- [ ] Commit as a single atomic commit: `refactor(<pkg>): split <old> into <a> and <b>`.

